  "prompt": "What instrument is used to measure volume?",
  "response": "The instrument used to measure volume depends on the state of the material being measured:\n\n1. **Liquid Volume**: Graduated cylinders, measuring cups, pipettes, and burettes are commonly used to measure the volume of liquids.\n\n2. **Solid Volume**: For irregularly shaped solids, a displacement method can be used, often involving a graduated cylinder filled with water. The change in water level indicates the volume of the solid. For regular solids, mathematical formulas (length \u00d7 width \u00d7 height for cubes, for example) can be used.\n\n3. **Gas Volume**: Gas volumes can be measured using gas syringes, manometers, or flow meters, depending on the context.\n\nIn general, the specific instrument will depend on the type of substance and the required precision of the measurement.",
